						<p><hi rend="italic">Two fragments built into the front wall of the temple of Īśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI—A.D. 1096.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription dated in the <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 2[1]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1096,</hi> records a gift of certain taxes. The details of the gift are lost. The division of <hi rend="bold">Banavāse Twelve-thousand</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

